## 2. Project Deep Dives

### рҹ”— 1. `zippycoin-core` вҖ” L1 Blockchain Node
**Path:** `S:\Projects\zippycoin-core`
**Remote:** `https://github.com/GoZippy/zippycoin-core.git`
**Branch:** `master` | **Build:** `cargo check` вң… PASSES

**Purpose:** The primary ZippyCoin Layer 1 blockchain node, implemented in Rust. This is the source of truth for on-chain state, consensus, and protocol execution.

**Key Subdirectories:**
- `packages/blockchain/src/` вҖ” Active node codebase (v1.0.0 simplified node)
- `packages/blockchain/legacy/` вҖ” Advanced BFT consensus engine (preserved for future migration)
- `packages/contracts/` вҖ” Solidity smart contracts
- `layer2/` вҖ” L2 / ZippyEdge integration scaffolding
- `services/` вҖ” Backend microservices (API Gateway, Trust Engine, DeFi, etc.)
- `infra/` вҖ” Proxmox VM deployment configs
- `docs/` вҖ” Architecture and production task lists
- `docs/COMPREHENSIVE_PRODUCTION_TASK_LIST.md` вҖ” Detailed pending task list

**Tech Stack:** Rust В· Tokio В· Axum В· RocksDB В· SHA3 В· CRYSTALS-Dilithium В· CRYSTALS-Kyber

**Protocol:**
- Consensus: Trust-Weighted DPoS
- Block Time: 12s (settlement L1) / 2s (edge/internal)
- Chain ID: `777`
- RPC Port: `8545` (JSON-RPC 2.0 + custom `zippy_*` methods)
- P2P Port: `30303`
- Cryptography: NIST Level 3 Quantum-Resistant (Dilithium signatures + Kyber key exchange)

**Custom RPC Extensions:** `zippy_getTrustScore` В· `zippy_getEnvironmentalData` В· `zippy_getValidatorStatus`

**Current Status:** Compiles and runs. Block production loop, P2P peer sync, and state persistence (JSONL chunked blocks) are all operational on local Proxmox VM cluster.

**Open TODOs:**
- [ ] Complete `broadcast_to_peers` in legacy consensus
- [ ] Implement Merkle proof verification in `verify_validator_data_integrity`
- [ ] Finish `finalize_block_static` implementation
- [ ] GraphQL + WebSocket support in API Gateway service
- [ ] Complete Trust Engine full pipeline
- [ ] Deploy contracts to public testnet

